attributes.Long form description: The student is disassembling a shelf. He removes the rotary wheels and brackets, then the trays, bottom bracket, and base. Finally, he removes the side bars.

attributes.Transcription: Hello, welcome to our study. In front of you, you will see a bathroom cabinet  from IKEA and your task for now will be to please assemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first pair of rotary wheels from the shelf.
The student disassembles the second pair of rotary wheels on the shelf.
The student disassemble the bracket of the shelf.
The student disassembles the bracket of the shelf.
The student disassembles the third bracket of the shelf.
The student disassembles the fourth bracket of the shelf.
The student disassembles the first  grid tray  of the shelf.
The student disassembles the second grid tray of the shelf.
The student disassembles one side of the bottom bracket of the shelf.
The student disassembles the second side of the bottom bracket of the shelf.
The student disassembles the bottom grid tray of the shelf.
The student disassembles the first part of the base of the shelf.
The student disassembles the half frame.
The student disassembles the side bars from the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: Thank you very much that was everything for this task.
You can now press the stop button.
